<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Violation occurs if struct Session declares value_1 and value_2 as non-const char * (e.g. char *value_1, *value_2). In the fragment these members are only read (passed to strlen/snprintf), so they should be declared as const char * to satisfy MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. SECOND_PAGE (a string literal) is already effectively const and is acceptable.
</scenario>

